# Blank Infinity Gauntlet

The [Blank Infinity Gauntlet](#blank-infinity-gauntlet) doesn’t do anything on its own, but is still an essential part to obtaining the fully powered version.

## Crafting

To craft the [Blank Infinity Gauntlet](#blank-infinity-gauntlet), you need to [Forge](#forging) it by throwing 10 Gold Blocks, 3 Redstone Blocks, and the [Iron Hammer](#iron-hammer) on a lit Blast Furnace. (See video below.)

**![][image1]**

# Infinity Stones {#infinity-stones}

The [Infinity Stones](#infinity-stones) are an essential part to making the fully [Powered Infinity Gauntlet](#powered-infinity-gauntlet). Like the [Blank Infinity Gauntlet](#blank-infinity-gauntlet), the stones do not do anything on their own, but are all essential to obtaining it.

## Crafting

To craft the [Infinity Stones](#infinity-stones), throw a crafting table on top of an upwards facing barrel containing any of the stone’s recipe and push a piston downward onto the crafting table to get that recipe’s respective stone inside the barrel. (See videos below.)

# Powered Infinity Gauntlet {#powered-infinity-gauntlet}

The [Powered Infinity Gauntlet](#powered-infinity-gauntlet) is the main attraction of this Datapack and allows the wielder to gain incredible powers that will be useful in daily life as well as in PVP battles. Though because of its long creation process, it would be good sportsmanship to give back a gauntlet to its rightful owner upon their death.

## Crafting

To craft the [Powered Infinity Gauntlet](#powered-infinity-gauntlet), simply throw all six [Infinity Stones](#infinity-stones) on the ground along with the [Blank Infinity Gauntlet](#blank-infinity-gauntlet). (See video below.)  
![][image10]

## Usage

Using the [Powered Infinity Gauntlet](#powered-infinity-gauntlet) is quite simple, though if the user is not careful, could result in an accidental death. Right-click (or place block key) with the [Powered Infinity Gauntlet](#powered-infinity-gauntlet) in your main hand to cycle through which [Infinity Stone](#infinity-stones) you are currently using. Hold shift (or sneak key) and right-click (or place block key) with the [Powered Infinity Gauntlet](#powered-infinity-gauntlet) in your off-hand to cycle through which [ability](#abilities) you are currently using (all stones except the [Mind Stone](#mind-stone) have more than one [ability](#abilities).) And finally, right-click (or place block key) with the [Powered Infinity Gauntlet](#powered-infinity-gauntlet) in your off-hand to activate the selected ability. You can hold down right-click (or place block key) to continuously activate the selected [ability](#abilities).

## Abilities {#abilities}

### Time Stone:

* #### *Slow Time*

  * Grants Slowness V for 2 seconds, Slow Falling for 2 seconds, and Mining Fatigue for 2 seconds to anyone in a 3 block radius including the user, but also grants Speed VII for 2 seconds, and Haste II for 2 seconds to the user only. 

* #### *Stop Day Cycle*

  * Stops the day cycle.

* #### *Start Day Cycle*

  * Starts the day cycle.

* #### *Fast Forward Day Cycle*

  * Speeds up the day cycle for the duration the ability is active.

* #### *Set Time to Noon*

  * Sets the in-game time to noon.

### Power Stone:

* #### *Small Fireball*

  * Shoots a small/blaze fireball projectile in the direction the user is looking.

* #### *Large Fireball*

  * Shoots a large/ghast fireball projectile in the direction the user is looking.

* #### *Dragon Fireball*

  * Shoots a dragon/ender dragon fireball projectile in the direction the user is looking.

* #### *Ray Burst*

  * Shoots an explosive purple projectile in the direction the user is looking.

### Space Stone:

* #### *Quick Teleport*

  * Teleports the user 5 blocks forward in the direction they are looking and gives the user Slow Falling and Levitation for 1 second.

* #### *Medium Teleport*

  * Teleports the user 15 blocks forward in the direction they are looking and gives the user Slow Falling for 1 second.

* #### *Far Teleport*

  * Teleports the user 25 blocks forward in the direction they are looking and gives the user Slow Falling for 1 second.

* #### *Hold Entity/Release Entity*

  * Continuously teleports the closest entity within 5 blocks 3 blocks in the direction the user is facing until the ability is disabled or the gauntlet is equipped.

### Reality Stone:

* #### *Terraform Floor*

  * Places a dirt block beneath your feet, destroying and dropping the block it replaces (doesn’t work with indestructible blocks).

* #### *Throw TNT*

  * Throws an ignited TNT block in the direction you are looking.

* #### *Configure Enchantments* {#configure-enchantments}

  * This ability only appears once the wielder of the [Powered Infinity Gauntlet](#powered-infinity-gauntlet) holds either the [Power Stone Infused Netherite Sword](#power-stone-infused-netherite-sword), [Reality Stone Infused Netherite Multitool](#reality-stone-infused-netherite-multitool), [Reality Stone Infused Netherite Pickaxe](#reality-stone-shard-infused-netherite-pickaxe), [Reality Stone Infused Netherite Axe](#reality-stone-shard-infused-netherite-axe), [Reality Stone Infused Netherite Shovel](#reality-stone-shard-infused-netherite-shovel), or [Reality Stone Infused Netherite Hoe](#reality-stone-shard-infused-netherite-hoe) in their main hand. This ability cycles through “controversial” enchantments (such as Fire Aspect, Knockback, Fortune, and Silk Touch) on the current tool/weapon in the wielder’s main hand. 

* #### *Configure Tool* {#configure-tool}

  * This ability only appears once the wielder of the [Powered Infinity Gauntlet](#powered-infinity-gauntlet) holds the [Reality Stone Infused Multitool](#reality-stone-infused-netherite-multitool) in their main hand. This ability cycles through the tools on the [Reality Stone Infused Multitool](#reality-stone-infused-netherite-multitool) in the wielder’s main hand. 

### Soul Stone:

* #### *Decay Soul*

  * Grants Wither II for 5 seconds to anyone in a 5 block radius including the user, but also grants Regeneration V for 5 seconds to the user only.

* #### *Detect Soul*

  * Grants Glowing I for 1 second to all entities (that have a soul) in a 10 block radius including the user.

### Mind Stone:

The [Mind Stone](#mind-stone) acts as a default state where you gain all the passive effects of having the [Powered Infinity Gauntlet](#powered-infinity-gauntlet) in your off-hand without accidentally activating an ability.

### Passive Effects:

* Dolphin’s Grace  
* Speed I  
* Resistance I  
* Fire Resistance I  
* Conduit Power  
* Night Vision  
* Regeneration III  
* Strength I

* #### *Lure of the Simple Minded*

  * Pigs will be lured to the wielder of the [Powered Infinity Gauntlet](#powered-infinity-gauntlet).

* #### *Satisfied Hunger*

  * Your hunger will never tick down so long as it is at full.

* #### *Unavoidable*

  * When falling into the void, (beneath y= \-65) the user will be teleported up 100 blocks from their current location and given slow falling for 5 seconds.  
  * Also applies to [Invulnerable Items](#invulnerable-items) falling into the void (beneath y= \-33).

# Iron Hammer {#iron-hammer}

A tool used to Forge and Break items like the Blank Infinity Gauntlet, [Infinity Stones](#infinity-stones), and tools/weapons.  
![][image13]

## Recipe

To craft the [Iron Hammer](#iron-hammer), you simply need to throw 2 [Reinforced Sticks](#reinforced-stick) along with 5 Iron Blocks on the ground. (See video below.)  
![][image14]

## Usage

Used in the recipe for the [Power Stone Infused Netherite Sword](#power-stone-infused-netherite-sword), [Reality Stone Infused Netherite Multitool](#reality-stone-infused-netherite-multitool), [Reality Stone Shard Infused Netherite Pickaxe](#reality-stone-shard-infused-netherite-pickaxe), [Reality Stone Shard Infused Netherite Axe](#reality-stone-shard-infused-netherite-axe), [Reality Stone Shard Infused Netherite Shovel](#reality-stone-shard-infused-netherite-shovel), and the [Reality Stone Shard Infused Netherite Hoe](#reality-stone-shard-infused-netherite-hoe).

# Power Stone Infused Netherite Sword {#power-stone-infused-netherite-sword}

The [Power Stone](#power-stone) and a Netherite Sword fused together to make the most powerful weapon in the world. As well as being unbreakable, it automatically comes with the enchantments: Sharpness IX, Looting III, Sweeping Edge III, Fire Aspect III, and Knockback III.  
![][image15]

## Recipe

To craft the [Power Stone Infused Netherite Sword](#power-stone-infused-netherite-sword), simply throw the [Iron Hammer](#iron-hammer), a Netherite Sword, and the [Power Stone](#power-stone) on the ground together. Once the recipe is finished, you will keep the [Iron Hammer](#iron-hammer). (See video below.)  
![][image16]

## Configure Enchantments Cycle

This weapon is able to be used with the [Powered Infinity Gauntlet](#powered-infinity-gauntlet)’s [Configure Enchantments](#configure-enchantments) ability to cycle through the “controversial” enchantments on this weapon. The “controversial” enchantments on this weapon are Fire Aspect and Knockback. The cycle goes:  
Fire Aspect III, Knockback III ➔ Fire Aspect III ➔ Knockback III ➔ None   
After none, it goes back to the first cycle setting.

# Reality Stone Infused Netherite Multitool {#reality-stone-infused-netherite-multitool}

The [Reality Stone](#reality-stone), a Netherite Pickaxe, a Netherite Axe, a Netherite Shovel, and a Netherite Hoe all fused together. With the power to shape reality and the strongest tools to add to it, nothing shall stand in the way of the wielder. As well as being unbreakable, it automatically comes with different enchantments depending on which tool is selected. This tool can also be [Broken](#breaking) into the [Reality Stone Shard Infused Netherite Pickaxe](#reality-stone-shard-infused-netherite-pickaxe), [Reality Stone Shard Infused Netherite Axe](#reality-stone-shard-infused-netherite-axe), [Reality Stone Shard Infused Netherite Shovel](#reality-stone-shard-infused-netherite-shovel), and [Reality Stone Shard Infused Netherite Hoe](#reality-stone-shard-infused-netherite-hoe).

![][image17]![][image18]  
![][image19]![][image20]

## Recipe

![][image21]

## Configure Enchantments Cycle

Each tool able to be swapped to with the [Reality Stone Infused Netherite Multitool](#reality-stone-infused-netherite-multitool) has base enchantments that come with it. All tools (including axes) have Efficiency IX and the axes exclusively have Sharpness IX. However, using the [Powered Infinity Gauntlet](#powered-infinity-gauntlet)’s [Configure Enchantments](#configure-enchantments) ability, each tool also cycles through the “controversial” enchantments on tools. The cycle goes:  
Silk Touch ➔ Fortune III  
After Fortune III, it goes back to the first cycle setting.

## Configure Tool Cycle

The main attraction to this tool is the multitool part of it. When using the [Powered Infinity Gauntlet](#powered-infinity-gauntlet)’s [Configure Tool](#configure-tool) ability, the current tool will cycle. The cycle goes:  
Pickaxe ➔ Axe ➔ Shovel ➔ Hoe  
After Hoe, it goes back to the first cycle setting.

# Reality Stone Shard Infused Netherite Tools {#reality-stone-shard-infused-netherite-tools}

[Reality Stone Shard Infused Netherite Tools](#reality-stone-shard-infused-netherite-tools) are broken versions of the [Reality Stone Infused Netherite Multitool](#reality-stone-infused-netherite-multitool). After breaking the [Reality Stone Infused Netherite Multitool](#reality-stone-infused-netherite-multitool) (using the [Breaking](#breaking) process below), it will turn into 4 [Reality Stone Shard Infused Netherite Tools](#reality-stone-shard-infused-netherite-tools). Alternatively, you can just build each individual [Reality Stone Shard Infused Netherite Tool](#reality-stone-shard-infused-netherite-tools) by [Forging](#forging) it with its respective [Forging](#forging) recipe.

# Invulnerable Items {#invulnerable-items}

[Invulnerable Items](#invulnerable-items) are items that cannot be deleted/destroyed by being thrown into a cactus, fire/lava, explosions, or being dropped into the void.   
Invulnerable Items include: 

* [Powered Infinity Gauntlet](#powered-infinity-gauntlet)  
* [Time Stone](#time-stone)  
* [Time Stone Shard](#time-stone-shard)  
* [Power Stone](#power-stone)

# Breaking {#breaking}

[Breaking](#breaking) is a crafting process by which one item, along with the [Iron Hammer](#iron-hammer), on top of any Anvil becomes multiple items.

# Forging {#forging}

[Forging](#forging) is a crafting process by which multiple items, along with the [Iron Hammer](#iron-hammer), on top of a lit Blast Furnace becomes one item.
